For what it's worth, I know  is a trope so popular on this site that it's rapidly approaching cliche. I was close to abandoning this project early on for those reasons, but people seemed to like the manuscript enough that I was encouraged to go for it. But I'll admit this piece is leaning very hard on the manuscript, which is why I spent a lot of time and effort on that section in particular. I wrote most of the prop on the subway and probably creeped some commuters out with my arts and crafts time, heh.

I'm of the opinion that solid execution can overcome the fact that an idea has been done before. I'm glad all the effort I put into  manuscript at least saved me from your down vote. I knew going in this wouldn't be everyone's cup of tea, so I'm going to round this up to a win.





